# 🔹 Why Complexity Analysis?

When multiple algorithms solve the same problem, we choose the most efficient one.

Complexity measures:

### 1️⃣ Time Complexity

Execution time growth with input size.

### 2️⃣ Space Complexity

Extra memory required.

---

# 🔹 Asymptotic Notations

---

## Big-O Notation (Upper Bound)

Represents worst-case complexity.

Examples:

[
O(1)
]

[
O(\log n)
]

[
O(n)
]

[
O(n\log n)
]

[
O(n^2)
]

---

## Big-Ω (Omega)

Best-case complexity.

---

## Big-Θ (Theta)

Tight bound.

---

📌 GATE frequently asks difference between O, Ω and Θ.

---

# 🔹 Complexity Order (Most Important)

From best to worst:

[
O(1)
<
O(\log n)
<
O(n)
<
O(n\log n)
<
O(n^2)
<
O(2^n)
<
O(n!)
]

